Set net-scale-factor=0.00390625 (1/256), offsets=128;128;128 and model-color-format=1.
Great, I think that's correct setting. 
It can starts to detect keypoints.

However, I tried many convertsion method, I change network input size to (1,3,256,256) or (1,3,256,456) during conversion to onnx.

Then I also tried the following.
void *cmap_data = tensor_meta->out_buf_ptrs_host[2];
NvDsInferDims &cmap_dims = tensor_meta->output_layers_info[2].inferDims;
void *paf_data = tensor_meta->out_buf_ptrs_host[3];
NvDsInferDims &paf_dims = tensor_meta->output_layers_info[3].inferDims;

or

void *cmap_data = tensor_meta->out_buf_ptrs_host[0];
NvDsInferDims &cmap_dims = tensor_meta->output_layers_info[0].inferDims;
void *paf_data = tensor_meta->out_buf_ptrs_host[1];
NvDsInferDims &paf_dims = tensor_meta->output_layers_info[1].inferDims;


It seems to detect only half data.
Actually, I wanna ask why network needs four output, and then using half output. Maybe that's reason? Because I used the first two output or the last two output, but displaying the same effect. 

Maybe network needs to been changed to two output?


